WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.091
.

00:04.134 --> 00:06.267
- Previously
on "Good Girls"...

00:06.310 --> 00:07.616
- I told you everything I know.

00:07.659 --> 00:10.793
- Pack your kids up.
I'm booking you tonight.

00:10.836 --> 00:12.708
- One of them's married
to a cop.

00:12.751 --> 00:14.797
- I want you out.
- Not an option.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.451
- No more pen cap.

00:16.494 --> 00:18.453
There's no saving my soul.
I'm already going to hell.

00:18.496 --> 00:20.629
- He said
there's someone else.

00:20.672 --> 00:22.500
- Hey, they were
out of cinnamon, so...

00:22.544 --> 00:24.676
- I'm the dick
who slept with your dad.

00:24.720 --> 00:26.504
- What?

00:26.548 --> 00:28.506
- Did you forgive him?
- I think I did.

00:28.550 --> 00:30.247
- You're a better person
than me.

00:30.291 --> 00:33.381
- How many women did my husband
cheat on me with?

00:33.424 --> 00:36.732
- Including Amber?
Four.

00:36.775 --> 00:38.777
- [moaning]

00:38.821 --> 00:41.476
I think the dealership
could be great again.

00:41.519 --> 00:43.086
Buy with fake
and sell for real,

00:43.130 --> 00:45.175
and we'll take a cut.
- Cars for cash.

00:45.219 --> 00:48.570
- Then come on down to the new
and improved Boland Motors.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.180
I've been working
on your calendar.

00:50.224 --> 00:52.487
- Where are you going to be?
- Here, at work.

00:52.530 --> 00:54.663
We can't both steer the ship.

00:56.578 --> 00:59.363
- You guys--No!
No mustaches in the morning.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.191
There's no--
Come on, you guys.

01:01.235 --> 01:02.410
Did you brush your teeth?

01:02.453 --> 01:03.628
No, you didn't
brush your teeth.

01:03.672 --> 01:05.195
I can smell it from here.
Here.

01:05.239 --> 01:07.197
And pants, young lady.
You need pants.

01:07.241 --> 01:08.546
What is your deal
with the pants?

01:08.590 --> 01:10.809
Kenny!
Hey, K-Man!

01:10.853 --> 01:12.768
Do not forget your
homework upstairs.

01:12.811 --> 01:14.552
All right, guys,
let's get breakfast.

01:14.596 --> 01:19.514
Oh, Dad forgot milk, so we're
gonna do it dry, okay?

01:19.557 --> 01:22.125
Just--it's just as delicious,
just not as wet.

01:22.169 --> 01:23.779
- [on TV] On-site day care
while you shop.

01:23.822 --> 01:26.129
- There you go.
And here's some.

01:26.173 --> 01:28.349
I'll clean that up.

01:28.392 --> 01:31.743
- Hey, you guys, look.
Mommy's on TV

01:31.787 --> 01:33.832
- Oh.
- Yay!

01:33.876 --> 01:36.792
- Our flexible hours will suit
any woman's schedule,

01:36.835 --> 01:39.751
whether you're stuck
at ho--

01:39.795 --> 01:42.711
Where are the lunches?
- Um...

01:44.278 --> 01:46.584
Oh...

01:46.628 --> 01:49.805
- Okay, it's a hot-lunch day.
- Who's gonna do my hair?

01:49.848 --> 01:52.416
- Daddy's going to.
- Here.

01:52.460 --> 01:54.244
- But he can't do
the bun for ballet.

01:54.288 --> 01:56.768
- He'll learn.
- I will--I will learn.

01:56.812 --> 01:58.596
- All right, love you.
- Give me your face. Come here.

01:58.640 --> 02:00.772
- Mwah.
Love you. I love you.

02:00.816 --> 02:04.124
- Hey, are you gonna be late?
- Don't wait up.

02:04.167 --> 02:06.778
[door opens, closes]

02:06.822 --> 02:09.433
- [sighs]
Good morning, Mrs. Boland.

02:09.477 --> 02:11.653
- How's the baby?
- Not sleeping, Mrs. Boland.

02:11.696 --> 02:13.437
- Told you--white noise,

02:13.481 --> 02:15.613
blackout curtains,
and let him cry.

02:15.657 --> 02:17.267
- [chuckles]
- Morning, Ms. Boland.

02:17.311 --> 02:20.270
[indistinct chatter]

02:20.314 --> 02:22.925
[music playing faintly]

02:22.968 --> 02:28.626
♪

02:28.670 --> 02:30.628
- How can I help you?

02:30.672 --> 02:33.936
- Yeah, I got some cars
coming in today from up north.

02:33.979 --> 02:36.373
- What kind of cars?
- Ah, blue ones, green ones.

02:36.417 --> 02:38.288
You know.
- Well, my lot's full.

02:38.332 --> 02:41.726
- Yeah, these
are for me, though.

02:41.770 --> 02:43.467
- What do you mean?

02:43.511 --> 02:46.557
- You know, you don't got
to worry about all that stuff.

02:46.601 --> 02:49.212
Just stay
in your little lane.

02:49.256 --> 02:52.563
I am going to need you to
deliver me one, though, yeah?

02:54.739 --> 02:56.480
- What did you put
in the cars?

02:56.524 --> 02:58.308
- [scoffs] Why I got to push
ten different buttons

02:58.352 --> 02:59.831
to get a cappuccino?
[chuckles]

02:59.875 --> 03:01.833
Mocha--no.
Vanilla--no.

03:01.877 --> 03:04.401
- What's in the cars?
- "What's in the box?

03:04.445 --> 03:07.926
What's in the box?"
[chuckles]

03:07.970 --> 03:11.539
Just bring them, all right?

03:11.582 --> 03:14.759
It won't be good for nobody
if you don't.

03:15.891 --> 03:18.589
Love what you've done
with the place.

03:20.548 --> 03:22.854
[Fassine's
"Bring the Weight Down"]

03:22.898 --> 03:25.857
[car carrier rattling]

03:25.901 --> 03:32.734
♪

03:35.040 --> 03:38.870
- ♪ Wave the Flag,
wear the mask ♪

03:38.914 --> 03:41.873
♪

03:41.917 --> 03:45.529
♪ Move slowly
through the past ♪

03:45.573 --> 03:48.706
♪

03:48.750 --> 03:52.884
♪ Oh, yeah,
bring the weight down ♪

03:52.928 --> 03:58.020
♪

03:58.063 --> 03:59.891
♪ I'm on fire

03:59.935 --> 04:03.765
♪

04:03.808 --> 04:06.594
♪ Bring the weight down

04:06.637 --> 04:10.902
♪

04:10.946 --> 04:11.990
♪ I'm on f--

04:12.034 --> 04:13.949
[music stops]

04:32.097 --> 04:34.274
[brakes squeal]

04:34.317 --> 04:35.666
- What are you doing here?

04:35.710 --> 04:37.320
- Well, I-I have
a surprise for you.

04:37.364 --> 04:38.626
- Nancy's picking me up.

04:38.669 --> 04:40.454
- Well, I think
you're going to like it.

04:42.020 --> 04:45.067
Okay. You know how you've
always wanted a puppy?

04:45.110 --> 04:47.765
- You did not.
- I did not.

04:47.809 --> 04:49.854
But I am seriously open
to the possibility.

04:49.898 --> 04:51.378
- You're allergic.

04:51.421 --> 04:55.425
- I may or may not
have made that up.

04:55.469 --> 04:57.601
[scoffs] I'm sorry, it's--

04:57.645 --> 05:00.517
The new me is trying
to be 100% honest.

05:04.347 --> 05:06.306
- How is Nancy?
- Pregnant.

05:06.349 --> 05:08.612
- I mean, like, mentally.
Is she all right?

05:08.656 --> 05:10.092
- What do you think?
- [scoffs]

05:10.135 --> 05:11.659
How much longer
are you gonna stay there?

05:11.702 --> 05:13.095
- I don't know.

05:13.138 --> 05:14.792
- You know, I'm talking
to the turtle again.

05:14.836 --> 05:17.404
We're having deep conversations
about life and love.

05:17.447 --> 05:19.057
- Please. Just--just go.

05:19.101 --> 05:20.929
- [sighs] I'm sorry.
I made a bad decision.

05:20.972 --> 05:23.671
But you know
what Julia Ormond says.

05:23.714 --> 05:25.977
- Who's Julia Ormond?
- Not her.

05:26.021 --> 05:28.806
You know, the--the financial
lady with the rooster head?

05:28.850 --> 05:32.332
Anyway,
she says that bad decisions

05:32.375 --> 05:34.334
make teachable moments.

05:34.377 --> 05:36.597
- So what did you learn?

05:36.640 --> 05:39.948
- I learned
that I'm a complete idiot.

05:39.991 --> 05:41.863
And I miss you.

05:44.996 --> 05:46.563
And I'm lonely.

05:48.391 --> 05:50.915
- Nancy's lonely, too.

05:52.526 --> 05:54.702
- [sighs]

05:58.488 --> 06:01.143
- So now we're
in the delivery business.

06:01.186 --> 06:02.840
- [sighs]

06:02.884 --> 06:05.930
She's in a fog, man.

06:05.974 --> 06:08.455
- What the hell is
in those cars anyway?

06:08.498 --> 06:10.065
- Dong fog.

06:10.108 --> 06:13.024
It's eating her brain.
- I mean, fake cash, sure.

06:13.068 --> 06:15.679
- Ugh. I can't even stand
to watch them together.

06:15.723 --> 06:19.509
- But what else--
like, guns, people?

06:19.553 --> 06:21.381
- She presents like a baboon.

06:23.470 --> 06:26.124
You know,
with the flared anus.

06:27.474 --> 06:29.519
- Never, ever say that word.

06:29.563 --> 06:31.565
- Which--
"flared" or "anus"?

06:31.608 --> 06:34.568
- Either.
[footsteps approaching]

06:37.092 --> 06:38.920
- [sighs]
- So what's in the car?

06:38.963 --> 06:40.965
- Nothing.
- What do you mean "nothing"?

06:41.009 --> 06:42.706
- I mean, obviously something,

06:42.750 --> 06:44.795
but I tore
every single one apart.

06:44.839 --> 06:46.884
- Shady S.O.B.

06:46.928 --> 06:48.538
- "Stay in your lane."

06:48.582 --> 06:50.192
I am in my lane.
- Yeah, you are.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.150
- He's in my lane.
- Yeah, he is.

06:52.194 --> 06:54.065
- 'Cause you know
who's gonna go down for this

06:54.109 --> 06:55.937
when he gets caught smuggling
whatever it is he's smuggling.

06:55.980 --> 06:58.635
- Yeah, you.
Well, us.

07:00.898 --> 07:03.161
- Hey, there he is.

07:06.077 --> 07:07.862
- What's he doing?

07:13.911 --> 07:15.870
- Hey, now.

07:17.262 --> 07:20.962
- Ooh. Nuh-uh.
- Yuh-huh.

07:23.965 --> 07:26.924
- Hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

07:32.843 --> 07:34.932
Sweetie,
it's probably just business.

07:34.976 --> 07:36.934
- Yeah, I mean,
what do they say?

07:36.978 --> 07:39.067
You know, why make a sale when
you can make a loyal customer?

07:39.110 --> 07:43.114
- Right, I mean, relationships
are everything in, you know...

07:43.158 --> 07:45.073
- The biz.
- Yeah.

07:45.116 --> 07:48.163
[engine turning over]

07:52.297 --> 07:53.777
- Hey, maybe we should grab
a snack or, like,

07:53.821 --> 07:55.126
a smoothie or something.
- I'm so hungry.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.041
- Drive.
[engine turning over]

07:59.522 --> 07:59.914
.

07:59.957 --> 08:02.525
[fast hip-hop music]

08:02.569 --> 08:09.619
♪

08:24.634 --> 08:28.420
- What, next point wins?
- You better D up.

08:28.464 --> 08:30.248
- Oh!
- Yay!

08:30.292 --> 08:32.686
Good game, baby.

08:32.729 --> 08:36.211
[grunts]
- Anybody got next?

08:36.254 --> 08:38.561
[man speaking indistinctly
over PA]

08:38.605 --> 08:40.302
- [exhales sharply]

08:40.345 --> 08:43.610
You know what?
Maybe next time. I got to...

08:43.653 --> 08:45.307
- Promise to take it easy.

08:45.350 --> 08:47.004
- Well, no,
I got my shift so...

08:47.048 --> 08:49.093
- Ah, you worried you might
get schooled, huh?

08:49.137 --> 08:51.269
- [chuckles]
- Come on, quick game to three.

08:51.313 --> 08:52.706
- Uh...

08:52.749 --> 08:55.578
Three, huh?
- Quick game to three.

08:55.622 --> 08:58.450
- Okay.
Did play in college?

08:58.494 --> 09:00.278
- Let's just say
I'm still bitter

09:00.322 --> 09:02.106
that Carolina took
Jordan over me.

09:02.150 --> 09:04.239
Oh!
[chuckles]

09:06.415 --> 09:08.286
- Looks like they made
the right choice.

09:08.330 --> 09:10.462
[both chuckle]
- Where you from?

09:10.506 --> 09:12.160
- 313,
born and raised.

09:12.203 --> 09:15.293
- Ooh.
You married?

09:16.381 --> 09:18.514
- Yep.

09:18.558 --> 09:21.473
- How long?
- 22 years.

09:21.517 --> 09:25.042
[rim rattles, net swishes]
- Whoo! 22.

09:25.086 --> 09:28.132
How many good years?
- All of them good.

09:28.176 --> 09:30.744
- All of them good?
Lucky man.

09:30.787 --> 09:33.703
Must be hard
being married to a cop.

09:33.747 --> 09:36.488
- You know what? I should
probably get out of here--

09:36.532 --> 09:38.316
- No, no, no, come on, man.
Come on, man.

09:38.360 --> 09:40.362
I haven't rolled with somebody
who can actually play ball

09:40.405 --> 09:42.059
since Baltimore.

09:44.018 --> 09:46.368
You know what I miss the most?
- What's that?

09:46.411 --> 09:48.631
- Ah. The food.

09:48.675 --> 09:50.764
[grunts]
[net swishes]

09:50.807 --> 09:52.156
- The food?
We got the best Coney dog

09:52.200 --> 09:53.984
game in the world here.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.464
- Yeah,
I been living off of them.

09:55.507 --> 09:57.727
- Yeah? Lafayette or American?
- Lafayette.

09:57.771 --> 09:59.642
- You complaining?

09:59.686 --> 10:02.166
- Well, I'm just more of a...

10:02.210 --> 10:05.561
home-cooked-meal
kind of guy--Oh!

10:05.605 --> 10:07.084
[sighs]

10:07.128 --> 10:09.609
Your wife got
cooking skills, huh?

10:09.652 --> 10:12.350
- My wife?
Uh...

10:13.482 --> 10:16.354
Yeah, yeah,
I mean, yeah, for--yeah.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.182
- What's her go-to?

10:18.226 --> 10:20.184
- You know, um...

10:20.228 --> 10:22.796
[stammers] Lasagna, whatever.

10:22.839 --> 10:25.059
- Oh, boom.
[net swishes]

10:25.102 --> 10:28.062
Game.
- Good game.

10:28.105 --> 10:30.020
- You didn't say lasagna,
did you?

10:30.064 --> 10:33.763
- Uh...yeah, I guess I--did I?
I said that?

10:33.807 --> 10:35.678
- That's like my death row meal
right there.

10:35.722 --> 10:36.810
- That's your jam
right there, huh?

10:36.853 --> 10:38.550
- Oh, yeah.
- [laughs]

10:38.594 --> 10:41.466
Home-cooked.
Yeah.

10:45.122 --> 10:47.342
- Look girl, if you
don't stop moving your head...

10:47.385 --> 10:50.562
So which one is Alex again?
- You always forget.

10:50.606 --> 10:52.390
- Curly afro or zitty braces?

10:52.434 --> 10:56.220
- Afro!
- Okay, chill.

10:56.264 --> 10:58.832
- Janelle says he likes me.

10:58.875 --> 11:03.401
- "What is your favorite food?
Mine is pizza."

11:03.445 --> 11:07.710
- You think?
- Oh, it's on.

11:07.754 --> 11:11.192
- But he put the same thing
in Rochelle's locker.

11:11.235 --> 11:14.108
- The same note...with all
those stupid questions?

11:14.151 --> 11:16.327
- Plus fav movie and fav song.

11:16.371 --> 11:18.721
- Let me tell you something
about the boys, baby girl.

11:18.765 --> 11:22.333
They love to put their stuff
in a whole bunch of lockers.

11:22.377 --> 11:24.205
- All at the same time?
- Oh, yeah.

11:24.248 --> 11:26.686
So, just when you think
your locker is special,

11:26.729 --> 11:28.775
they are working lockers
all over town.

11:28.818 --> 11:30.472
You know what I'm saying?

11:30.515 --> 11:32.430
Trying to keep
their options open,

11:32.474 --> 11:34.432
'cause there's a bunch out
there to choose from, right?

11:34.476 --> 11:36.217
Different sizes,
shapes, colors.

11:36.260 --> 11:37.697
- Ours all look the same.

11:37.740 --> 11:39.524
- And they don't even bother
to hide it now.

11:39.568 --> 11:41.875
Just all out in public,
all janky-like.

11:41.918 --> 11:45.487
So, if I were you, I would keep
that locker closed up tight

11:45.530 --> 11:47.228
for as long as possible.

11:47.271 --> 11:48.838
You hear me?

11:51.928 --> 11:54.148
Babe...

11:54.191 --> 11:56.280
it is so real out there
right now.

11:56.324 --> 11:59.457
- You like my hair, Daddy?
- I love it, baby.

11:59.501 --> 12:01.503
- Hey, y-you just about done?

12:01.546 --> 12:04.114
- You invited him to dinner?
- What was I supposed to do?

12:04.158 --> 12:05.507
- How about not do that?

12:05.550 --> 12:07.552
- He invited himself.

12:07.596 --> 12:09.511
- My name is
on that hostage list.

12:09.554 --> 12:11.861
- Your maiden name, right?

12:11.905 --> 12:14.559
- Yeah.
- Okay, so he might not know.

12:14.603 --> 12:16.300
- He's FBI, Stanley.

12:16.344 --> 12:18.302
- Babe, he--he--he wants
to bring his boyfriend.

12:18.346 --> 12:19.521
- So?
- So what's he gonna do--

12:19.564 --> 12:21.218
shake us down
at the dinner table?

12:21.262 --> 12:23.786
Maybe he just--
maybe it's just dinner.

12:23.830 --> 12:27.703
- Have you seen any episode
of "Columbo", like, ever?

12:27.747 --> 12:30.575
- [sighs]

12:38.845 --> 12:40.498
- What's this?

12:40.542 --> 12:43.937
- This? This is me not getting
hauled off in cuffs,

12:43.980 --> 12:46.896
me not doing life
without parole.

12:48.289 --> 12:49.812
And these?

12:49.856 --> 12:52.510
These are my children
not dressing up for Christmas

12:52.554 --> 12:54.730
to come visit me in prison.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.819
Your new bestie can enjoy
his home-cooked meal

12:56.863 --> 12:58.342
in his own home.

12:58.386 --> 12:59.822
- You want me to just
drop these off?

12:59.866 --> 13:01.389
- Yep.

13:01.432 --> 13:02.520
- 'Cause that's not
going to be weird.

13:02.564 --> 13:04.174
- I don't care.

13:04.218 --> 13:05.828
- He's gonna think
we're hiding something.

13:05.872 --> 13:08.831
- We are hiding something.
- [sighs]

13:08.875 --> 13:11.355
It's not a good look.

13:11.399 --> 13:13.227
- You want to know
what's not a good look?

13:13.270 --> 13:15.316
You at the dinner table
doing the shaky leg.

13:15.359 --> 13:17.971
- What are you talking about?
- You got no poker face, babe.

13:18.014 --> 13:19.581
And I love you for it,

13:19.624 --> 13:22.236
but it's gonna bring
the both of us down...hard.

13:26.501 --> 13:29.634
- I'll drop the dinner off.
- Yeah, you will.

13:38.687 --> 13:43.910
- ♪ What is the word?

13:43.953 --> 13:48.001
♪ An unhuman search

13:48.044 --> 13:50.873
♪

13:50.917 --> 13:56.487
♪ Memories touching

13:56.531 --> 13:58.402
♪

13:58.446 --> 14:01.492
♪ Heavy fog masking

14:01.536 --> 14:07.890
♪ I am a vessel

14:07.934 --> 14:09.674
♪

14:09.718 --> 14:14.984
♪ Are you a vessel?

14:15.028 --> 14:18.031
[toys squeaking]

14:18.074 --> 14:25.342
♪

14:42.316 --> 14:44.448
- I'm sorry,
I was gonna do that.

14:44.492 --> 14:46.276
- When?
- Uh...

14:46.320 --> 14:48.409
Well, I had to--
I had to make dinner.

14:48.452 --> 14:49.976
- It's not that complicated.

14:50.019 --> 14:51.673
- Well, and then I had
to get them in the bath

14:51.716 --> 14:52.979
and get them to bed.

14:53.022 --> 14:55.546
- No one wants
to come home to this.

14:55.590 --> 14:58.071
- Emma is upset about her hair,

14:58.114 --> 15:00.464
and Kenny is getting
his butt kicked in Krav Maga.

15:00.508 --> 15:02.640
And then Janey
won't wear pajamas.

15:02.684 --> 15:03.946
I don't know
if you noticed,

15:03.990 --> 15:05.687
but all that kid
likes to do right now is--

15:05.730 --> 15:07.776
- Yeah, I know. She does that.
- Yeah, well...

15:07.819 --> 15:09.734
while I'm reading
her bedtime stories?

15:09.778 --> 15:11.388
- It's her time.

15:11.432 --> 15:12.955
She just sits there,
like, with her hands--

15:12.999 --> 15:14.696
- It's normal, Dean.

15:14.739 --> 15:17.568
- Okay, well, I'm exhausted.
- Well, don't shame her.

15:17.612 --> 15:19.831
- It's exhausting.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.355
- Yeah.

15:28.536 --> 15:30.930
- I tried to put the booster
seats in the Malibu,

15:30.973 --> 15:32.583
but I couldn't
get Janey's to budge.

15:32.627 --> 15:34.455
- The latch gets stuck.
You've got to wiggle it.

15:34.498 --> 15:38.589
- When Danny is in the front
seat, I turn the air bags off

15:38.633 --> 15:40.896
and then keep them on
with Kenny--is that right?

15:40.940 --> 15:43.116
I just feel like the rules
keep changing.

15:43.159 --> 15:44.334
You okay?

15:44.378 --> 15:47.076
[upbeat music]

15:47.120 --> 15:52.821
♪

15:52.864 --> 15:55.867
[horn honks]

15:55.911 --> 16:02.874
♪

16:08.141 --> 16:09.664
[horn honks]

16:09.707 --> 16:12.145
[horn honking]

16:12.188 --> 16:19.413
♪

16:28.944 --> 16:31.468
[tires squeal]

16:33.122 --> 16:40.434
♪

16:59.409 --> 16:59.627
.

16:59.670 --> 17:02.021
- But I had the illest
second rebuttal, man.

17:02.064 --> 17:03.587
I was all like, "Guess what.

17:03.631 --> 17:06.155
"The imperative's on your ass.
There's no solvency here.

17:06.199 --> 17:08.201
"Your case is inherently
non-unique,

17:08.244 --> 17:11.334
and your argument
is moot, bitch!"

17:11.378 --> 17:14.076
- Whoo!
So did you win or what?

17:14.120 --> 17:17.036
- Headed to Nationals, dog.
- Nice.

17:17.079 --> 17:18.515
[both laugh]

17:18.559 --> 17:22.041
So my man here is, like,
a college-level debater.

17:22.084 --> 17:24.304
- Well, then this
is all kinds of wrong.

17:24.347 --> 17:27.350
- Can you tell us what it is?
- Um...

17:27.394 --> 17:31.093
I'm not getting
much of a reading here.

17:31.137 --> 17:34.053
- Think it's synthetic?
- Let's see.

17:35.228 --> 17:37.578
Fo sho.
- [sighs]

17:37.621 --> 17:39.188
- What does that even mean?

17:39.232 --> 17:42.452
Well, could be anything
from Special K, vitamin E,

17:42.496 --> 17:45.020
Kibbles and Bits, gamma-H,

17:45.064 --> 17:48.154
barbies, phennies,
roachies, egg rolls.

17:48.197 --> 17:49.372
- Okay, check it.

17:49.416 --> 17:51.200
This one right here--
- Yeah.

17:51.244 --> 17:55.074
- PD 155. It's like a statin
I think they call it.

17:55.117 --> 17:56.988
- Jesus.

17:58.164 --> 17:59.948
- What does that do to you?

17:59.991 --> 18:02.168
- It lowers cholesterol?

18:02.211 --> 18:03.473
- What, like, robo-tripping?

18:03.517 --> 18:05.214
Like, you got to pop
a ton of them or...?

18:05.258 --> 18:06.911
- I don't know.

18:06.955 --> 18:09.131
My--my dad just pops one
in the morning with milk.

18:09.175 --> 18:12.917
But, yeah, you--you got a
pretty diverse portfolio here.

18:12.961 --> 18:18.097
- Um, Prevacid, that's gonna be
for heartburn.

18:18.140 --> 18:20.055
Beta blockers for
blood pressure.

18:20.099 --> 18:22.188
Ooh, I think this might
actually be

18:22.231 --> 18:23.624
some sort
of antidepressant.

18:23.667 --> 18:26.931
Would have to cross-reference.
- I'm sorry.

18:26.975 --> 18:30.979
So these are all just,
like, normal-people drugs?

18:31.022 --> 18:32.415
- That's what it looks like.

18:32.459 --> 18:35.288
- So there's nothing here
that a junkie would want?

18:35.331 --> 18:38.160
- A junkie
with arterial plaque buildup?

18:41.468 --> 18:43.426
- Is this the statin
or the, um, blood pressure?

18:43.470 --> 18:47.213
I can't tell.
- Let me see here.

18:47.256 --> 18:50.259
Hmm.

18:50.303 --> 18:54.133
Hmm.
L 159...

18:54.176 --> 18:56.265
is a boner pill.

18:56.309 --> 18:59.225
- Great. Here's more.
- Thank you. [pops lips]

18:59.268 --> 19:01.618
- So we sell drugs now.
- Hmm.

19:01.662 --> 19:03.142
This one
doesn't have a number.

19:03.185 --> 19:06.667
- It might be an Altoid.
- Or Oxy.

19:08.190 --> 19:12.238
What if it was Oxy?
- [chuckling]

19:12.281 --> 19:14.414
- I am on the board
of D.A.R.E., okay?

19:14.457 --> 19:17.068
And the FBI guy has been
sniffing around Stan.

19:17.112 --> 19:19.549
- Well, does he have anything,
or is he just sniffing?

19:19.593 --> 19:22.204
- He loves to sniff.
- I don't know.

19:22.248 --> 19:24.206
But I can't afford to be
a drug dealer right now.

19:24.250 --> 19:26.165
- But these drugs
are good for people.

19:26.208 --> 19:28.167
- Who knew there was
a black market

19:28.210 --> 19:29.472
for, um, acid-reflux pills?

19:29.516 --> 19:31.735
Not me.
- It's pretty cool.

19:31.779 --> 19:34.216
- Are y'all for real?
- What? It's not fair.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.262
We deserve a cut.

19:36.305 --> 19:38.264
- 'Cause that's
what it's about.

19:40.266 --> 19:42.485
- What else would it be about?

19:42.529 --> 19:43.747
Drug Beth?

19:43.791 --> 19:45.619
- [scoffs]
Whatever.

19:45.662 --> 19:48.143
- Wait, what's Drug Beth?

19:48.187 --> 19:50.319
- Counterfeit Beth, Drug Beth,

19:50.363 --> 19:52.278
and you know
he's got a Gun Beth

19:52.321 --> 19:53.714
and a Blood Diamond Beth...
- Okay.

19:53.757 --> 19:55.237
- And a Human Trafficking Beth.

19:55.281 --> 19:57.326
- Let's just take it easy.

19:57.370 --> 20:00.199
- Oh, so now you're cool
with the fog?

20:00.242 --> 20:03.071
- Our values have realigned.

20:04.551 --> 20:06.640
- Our girl is a side piece.

20:06.683 --> 20:09.164
- You think I care
who he sleeps with?

20:09.208 --> 20:11.210
I so don't.

20:11.253 --> 20:12.689
I'm like--

20:12.733 --> 20:14.691
I'm like, "Who cares?"

20:14.735 --> 20:16.780
I don't--

20:16.824 --> 20:18.782
And he's making money
off our backs.

20:18.826 --> 20:21.524
- Yeah. Yeah, and with
our asses on the line.

20:21.568 --> 20:25.398
- So what? We just say,
"Cut us in, pretty please"?

20:25.441 --> 20:28.227
- No, we take every pill
from every car,

20:28.270 --> 20:30.141
and we bleed him dry.
- Hell, yeah.

20:30.185 --> 20:31.795
- And then he shoots us
in the face.

20:31.839 --> 20:33.754
- He can't shoot us in the face
if we have his product.

20:33.797 --> 20:35.451
- Can't he?
- He won't.

20:35.495 --> 20:37.105
- Won't he?

20:40.151 --> 20:42.284
[jazzy music]

20:42.328 --> 20:45.331
- Good morning, Mrs. Boland.
- Good morning, Linda.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.594
- Hey, guess what.
- What did I say?

20:47.637 --> 20:50.249
- I let him cry, and it worked.
- Told you.

20:50.292 --> 20:55.645
♪

20:55.689 --> 20:57.691
George?

20:57.734 --> 21:00.650
I would like you to show
my friend Darren here

21:00.694 --> 21:03.305
how to open
an air-bag compartment.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.785
- What?
- Yeah, I got a--

21:04.828 --> 21:07.266
I got a school project.

21:07.309 --> 21:14.316
♪

21:18.407 --> 21:21.584
- Yes!
- Keep it coming.

21:21.628 --> 21:28.678
♪

21:40.473 --> 21:42.779
[musical flourish]

21:42.823 --> 21:45.347
[brakes squeal]

21:45.391 --> 21:47.523
How was school?
- You're being a stalker.

21:47.567 --> 21:49.308
- Well, you're making me
be one.

21:49.351 --> 21:51.179
- It's weird.
- Well, I'd be a lot less weird

21:51.222 --> 21:55.226
if you'd just come home.
- Nancy's making vegan pizza.

21:55.270 --> 21:56.924
- You know she's
gonna try to slip you

21:56.967 --> 21:57.925
some of that nut cheese.

21:57.968 --> 22:00.406
- What do you want?

22:00.449 --> 22:02.364
- Can I just show you
something?

22:02.408 --> 22:05.541
Pick a prize!
Any prize.

22:05.585 --> 22:07.717
[children chattering
indistinctly]

22:07.761 --> 22:10.764
Look, I feel bad
that you feel bad,

22:10.807 --> 22:12.679
so I got you a present.

22:12.722 --> 22:14.724
- You got me a mall.

22:14.768 --> 22:17.292
- Well, look. Uh, here.

22:17.336 --> 22:20.164
Huh? It basically, like,
lives your entire life for you.

22:20.208 --> 22:21.949
It's obviously really dumb,

22:21.992 --> 22:24.386
but I feel like it's gonna make
all your friends super jelly.

22:24.430 --> 22:26.649
- How do you have
the money for this?

22:26.693 --> 22:28.434
- I picked up some
extra shifts.

22:28.477 --> 22:30.436
- At your grocery store?

22:30.479 --> 22:32.307
- Excuse me,
why do you say it like that?

22:32.351 --> 22:35.571
It is literally a grocery
store, and, you know,

22:35.615 --> 22:38.618
me and your auntie Beth
are working on something.

22:38.661 --> 22:40.315
- What?

22:40.359 --> 22:41.751
- Like a
"new business venture" thingy.

22:41.795 --> 22:43.623
- What?

22:43.666 --> 22:45.407
- We are diversifying
our portfolio,

22:45.451 --> 22:48.454
and I am projecting some
extremely sick profits, okay?

22:48.497 --> 22:49.846
- Now you're just saying
random words.

22:49.890 --> 22:51.413
- No, Sadie, I'm not.

22:51.457 --> 22:52.849
I'm trying to
explain to you, but I--

22:52.893 --> 22:55.417
- You're lying again.

22:55.461 --> 22:57.637
- What do you mean again?
- You lie about everything.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.378
- No, I don't.
- About Dad.

22:59.421 --> 23:01.510
Where you're going, why you're
late, why you're early.

23:01.554 --> 23:04.383
- I'm never early.
- You want me to come home?

23:04.426 --> 23:06.385
- Yes, please.

23:06.428 --> 23:08.474
- Tell me where
you got the money.

23:14.305 --> 23:16.395
- Does this mean
you don't want the watch?

23:17.918 --> 23:20.703
Sadie.

23:20.747 --> 23:22.313
[sighs]

23:22.357 --> 23:24.881
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

23:24.925 --> 23:26.883
- Ah, Mommy's home.
Hi, Mommy. Hey, babe.

23:26.927 --> 23:30.452
- Hi, Mommy.
- We've, uh--we got company.

23:32.933 --> 23:34.674
Say hi to Mommy.

23:36.806 --> 23:39.418
It's Agent Turner
and his boyfriend.

23:39.461 --> 23:42.421
[dramatic music]

23:42.464 --> 23:45.249
- [scoffs]

23:45.293 --> 23:49.776
- Well, I am happy to meet you.

23:49.819 --> 23:52.561
Call me Jimmy.
- Hi, there. Hi.

23:52.605 --> 23:55.434
- Mm, uh, this is Douglas.

23:55.477 --> 23:56.913
- How you doing?
- [chuckles]

23:56.957 --> 23:58.480
- Your kids are hilarious.

23:58.524 --> 23:59.742
- Yeah, Little Money
was playing

23:59.786 --> 24:01.570
his piano recital
for them...twice.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.398
- [chuckles]
Lucky you.

24:03.442 --> 24:04.965
- And you really put your foot
in the meal you sent us.

24:05.008 --> 24:07.271
Can always tell when something
is made with love.

24:07.315 --> 24:08.882
- Oh, that came through, huh?
- Mm.

24:08.925 --> 24:11.928
So I just had to say
thank you face-to-face.

24:11.972 --> 24:13.495
- Oh, it's not necessary.

24:13.539 --> 24:14.888
- Well, Rosemary Turner
would disagree.

24:14.931 --> 24:16.455
She would say,

24:16.498 --> 24:19.588
"Son, you never
return a dish empty."

24:19.632 --> 24:21.721
- Oh, uh,
you brought dinner?

24:21.764 --> 24:24.463
- Oh, yeah.
It's payback time.

24:24.506 --> 24:26.900
- [chuckles]
It's so nice, right?

24:26.943 --> 24:29.032
- [chuckles] So nice.
[man laughs]

24:29.076 --> 24:31.600
- Um...

24:31.644 --> 24:33.950
- You really made this
mac and cheese from scratch?

24:33.994 --> 24:35.517
- For real for real.

24:35.561 --> 24:36.823
- You think it's better
than the box?

24:36.866 --> 24:39.652
- I mean, the box stuff...

24:39.695 --> 24:42.393
[continues indistinctly]

24:47.573 --> 24:47.964
.

24:48.008 --> 24:50.097
[water running]

24:53.579 --> 24:55.798
[water stops]

24:55.842 --> 24:59.236
[door opens, closes]

24:59.280 --> 25:01.238
- Where is it?

25:01.282 --> 25:04.328
- I trusted you.
- That's your fault.

25:04.372 --> 25:06.330
- They're my cars.
- My money.

25:06.374 --> 25:09.899
- My dealership.
- Where is it?

25:09.943 --> 25:11.553
- Not here.

25:11.597 --> 25:13.555
- You know, I think this thing
with me and you

25:13.599 --> 25:15.514
has run its course, yeah?

25:15.557 --> 25:17.254
- Well, then you won't
get your pills.

25:17.298 --> 25:20.344
- I got more coming.
- Not in my cars, you don't.

25:21.607 --> 25:23.783
- Where is it?

25:23.826 --> 25:27.351
- I'll tell you
when you cut us in.

25:28.875 --> 25:31.878
- Oh, you think
you special, huh?

25:31.921 --> 25:33.444
- You need me.
- You ain't nothing.

25:33.488 --> 25:35.055
I don't need you.

25:35.098 --> 25:38.101
- So go buy a sketchy lot
down on Carson.

25:38.145 --> 25:41.278
Use fake cash,
staff it up with gang bangers.

25:41.322 --> 25:43.498
That won't look shady at all.

25:45.369 --> 25:47.284
How long do you think
till the Feds show up, huh?

25:47.328 --> 25:51.288
A month? A week?
They're already watching you.

25:51.332 --> 25:53.029
They just need a reason.

25:53.073 --> 25:55.989
[dramatic music]

25:56.032 --> 25:58.600
You need me
so they don't find one.

25:58.644 --> 26:01.298
♪

26:01.342 --> 26:02.996
[door opens]

26:03.039 --> 26:06.303
- Mama? Can you lay with me?

26:06.347 --> 26:09.306
- Yes, sweetie.
I promise.

26:13.310 --> 26:15.269
- Yeah.

26:24.278 --> 26:28.935
- Hey, okay.
Let's go get some popcorn.

26:28.978 --> 26:32.329
What the hell was that about?
- Business.

26:32.373 --> 26:35.506
- Did he--did he have a gun?

26:35.550 --> 26:37.813
- No.
- I think he did.

26:37.857 --> 26:40.381
- He was upset.
- Why?

26:40.424 --> 26:43.645
- Why what?
- Why him?

26:43.689 --> 26:45.604
- What are you
even talking about?

26:45.647 --> 26:47.388
- It's like you're
losing your mind.

26:47.431 --> 26:49.303
You're putting yourself
in these insane situations.

26:49.346 --> 26:51.261
Is it the tattoos?
Is that it?

26:51.305 --> 26:53.394
- Come on.
- The danger? The strange?

26:53.437 --> 26:56.527
I don't get it at all,
and I want to get it.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.399
- You know what I want to get?
- What?

26:58.442 --> 26:59.879
- What was it about Amber?

26:59.922 --> 27:01.576
- What does that have
to do with--

27:01.620 --> 27:04.492
Or anyone else at Team Boland
that sat on your penis.

27:09.715 --> 27:12.065
- [scoffs] I was lonely.

27:14.284 --> 27:16.417
And I didn't know
how to say it.

27:18.332 --> 27:20.377
- Well, you said something.

27:22.031 --> 27:23.990
- Loud and clear, huh?

27:25.469 --> 27:27.907
- It's business.

27:27.950 --> 27:29.691
- Okay.
- And it's for us.

27:29.735 --> 27:31.127
- Okay.

27:32.476 --> 27:35.044
My God.

27:35.088 --> 27:38.047
- So, uh,
Harry has this one buddy--

27:38.091 --> 27:39.396
- Frankie.
- Mm-hmm.

27:39.440 --> 27:41.137
Smallest one in the crew.

27:41.181 --> 27:43.226
- Causes big-time
trouble, though.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.576
- Right? But I had to get real
with Little Money

27:45.620 --> 27:47.230
and let him know
that at the end of the day,

27:47.274 --> 27:49.319
his buddy Frankie's skin
doesn't look like his.

27:49.363 --> 27:50.712
- Mm-hmm.
- You feel me?

27:50.756 --> 27:52.540
And so, when you are all
at the mall...

27:52.583 --> 27:54.977
[stammering]
And it goes sideways...

27:55.021 --> 27:56.979
- And you know it will.
- Mm-hmm.

27:57.023 --> 27:58.459
- You know, when they start
rounding folks up...

27:58.502 --> 27:59.678
- Where's Frankie going to be?

27:59.721 --> 28:01.549
- Home.
- And where are you?

28:01.592 --> 28:04.160
- Handcuffed on the curb
with a flashlight in your face.

28:04.204 --> 28:06.467
- Mm.
- I mean, he is only six.

28:06.510 --> 28:08.208
- All right, well, you know,

28:08.251 --> 28:09.949
it's never too young
to give the boy perspective.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.690
- So first day
of pre-K, right?

28:11.733 --> 28:13.169
- Oh, for you, that early?

28:13.213 --> 28:14.605
- Oh, Pops laid out
all the rules.

28:14.649 --> 28:16.607
Don't run with scissors,
don't play in the street,

28:16.651 --> 28:19.088
and don't get pissed when they
assume you're on financial aid.

28:19.132 --> 28:21.264
- I mean, but you were,
so there's that.

28:21.308 --> 28:22.918
[both laugh]

28:22.962 --> 28:24.528
- I don't know.

28:24.572 --> 28:26.443
- What? What don't
you know, baby?

28:26.487 --> 28:28.271
- That light in their eyes
right now.

28:28.315 --> 28:30.273
I don't want to put it out
so soon.

28:30.317 --> 28:32.536
- Either way it's going out.

28:34.364 --> 28:36.540
- That why you're a cop?

28:39.630 --> 28:41.110
- How you mean?

28:41.154 --> 28:43.983
- Show 'em you're
one of the good guys.

28:44.026 --> 28:45.549
- Hmm.

28:45.593 --> 28:47.116
Uh, maybe.

28:47.160 --> 28:48.509
[footsteps running]

28:48.552 --> 28:50.424
- Ladies and gentlemen,

28:50.467 --> 28:53.296
take your seats,
the show is about to begin.

28:53.340 --> 28:55.646
- Here we go.
- Tickets, please!

28:55.690 --> 28:56.778
- [laughs]

28:56.822 --> 28:58.693
I got a ticket.

28:58.737 --> 29:01.174
- There you are.
- [chuckles]

29:01.217 --> 29:03.132
- All right, good luck.

29:03.176 --> 29:05.134
- Now, how long you guys
been playing?

29:05.178 --> 29:06.788
- I've been playing four years.

29:06.832 --> 29:09.443
- [sighs]
How you doing?

29:09.486 --> 29:11.314
- You?

29:11.358 --> 29:13.490
- I'm good. [stammering]
I think we're good.

29:13.534 --> 29:16.711
- Daddy, come fix the bench.
He can't reach the peddles.

29:16.755 --> 29:19.758
- Huh? Oh, okay.
Copy.

29:26.068 --> 29:27.504
- Need a hand?

29:28.723 --> 29:30.420
- Concert's over already?

29:30.464 --> 29:32.771
- I think the maestro
is getting put to bed.

29:35.512 --> 29:38.341
- You got a good one in there.
- Yeah? I should keep him?

29:38.385 --> 29:40.517
- Mm-hmm.

29:40.561 --> 29:44.086
You guys are sweet together.
- Eh...

29:44.130 --> 29:48.134
20 years of marriage, you get
to know a person real good.

29:48.177 --> 29:50.049
- I bet.

29:52.312 --> 29:54.618
- I should have offered you
whipped cream.

29:56.229 --> 29:59.406
- It'll be worse for him.

29:59.449 --> 30:01.451
You get that, right?

30:06.108 --> 30:07.370
- Sorry?

30:07.414 --> 30:10.373
- When they find out
he took the pen cap.

30:10.417 --> 30:13.115
He don't look like
Lil Frankie either.

30:14.377 --> 30:16.727
The part that kills me
is that he just wants

30:16.771 --> 30:20.122
your son to look at him
and see a good cop.

30:23.430 --> 30:25.824
So you let me know
how you want to play it.

30:30.263 --> 30:33.092
[plates rattle]

30:33.135 --> 30:36.225
It's pie time, y'all.
- Hey, now!

30:36.269 --> 30:38.227
- I want whipped cream on mine!

30:38.271 --> 30:41.317
[indistinct chatter]

30:48.150 --> 30:48.542
.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.979
- And did you find everything
that you needed today?

